        <abstract>
            <p>Since dogs have same gestation period as the wolf it is likely that the wolf is the ancestral wild species, if it is just one species.</p> 
<p>CD’s belief that domestic dogs are descended from several distinct aboriginal species seems to contradict views on sterility of hybrids and variation in <hi rend="italic">Origin</hi>. If domestic varieties came from hybrids of wild species it will be impossible to trace ancestry. Opponents will exploit these problems.</p> 
        </abstract>
